    <stitle>13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14613 - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="9">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302776">Figure 76</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302776" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302776" filename="../figg13/g1302776.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 76. Input Shaft Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing retaining snap ring from the groove in the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302777">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302777" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302777" filename="../figg13/g1302777.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 77. Remove Bearing Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a rubber maul on the input shaft to cock the bearing in the bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302778">Figure 78</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302778" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302778" filename="../figg13/g1302778.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 78. Cock Bearing in Bore</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive input shaft toward rear of the transmission, through the bearing as far as possible (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302779">Figure 79</hotlnk>). Pull the input shaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302779" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302779" filename="../figg13/g1302779.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 79. Drive Input Shaft Toward Rear of Transmission</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pry bars or screwdrivers to complete removal of the bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302780">Figure 80</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302780" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302780" filename="../figg13/g1302780.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 80. Complete Removal of Bearing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302781">Figure 81</hotlnk>) and snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302781">inset, Figure 81</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302781" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302781" filename="../figg13/g1302781.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 81. Remove Drive Gear Spacer and Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the input shaft forward and out of the drive gear and case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302782">Figure 82</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302782" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302782" filename="../figg13/g1302782.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 82. Pull Input Shaft Forward</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the bushing in the pocket of the input shaft and replace if worn (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302783">Figure 83</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302783" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302783" filename="../figg13/g1302783.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 83. Check Bushing and Replace if Worn</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the main gear from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302784">Figure 84</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302784" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302784" filename="../figg13/g1302784.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 84. Remove Main Gear From Case</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
